FBIS4-38580 "drsov105_s_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-105 Daily Report 20 May 1994 Georgia National-Democratic Party Tops Party Popularity Poll National-Democratic Party Tops Party Popularity Poll AU3005204994 Tbilisi AKHALI TAOBA in Georgian 20 May 94 p 1 AU3005204994 Tbilisi AKHALI TAOBA Georgian BFN [Unattributed report on the results of an opinion poll: "The Population's Sympathies Lie With the Opposition"] [Text] At the beginning of May, a sociological survey was carried out with the aim of establishing the popularity rating of political parties. The following political organizations topped the poll: The National-Democratic Party, the Republican Party, and the Popular Front. It is significant that the Union of [Georgia's] Citizens that was widely publicized by the authorities and that is led by the present head of state was only in ninth place. As can be seen, the population's sympathies basically lean toward the opposition. This is also shown by the fact that eight of the 10 leading political organizations belong to the opposition. This shows once more that society is expecting significant changes in the government. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Popularity Rating of the Leading Political Organizations in Georgia | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | |negative assessment |positive assessment | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | |(percentage) | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |National-Democratic Party|-31.4 |44.6 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Republican Party |-38.1 |35.4 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Popular Front |-38.5 |31.6 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Merab Kostava Society |-50.9 |26.6 | ----------------------------------